fields.description:
When I try to remove a deploy key from Bitbucket project, I get an error dialog saying

{code}
Error

There was an error communicating with the server, please try again.
{code}

and the removing fails. I’ve tried refreshing page and logging out / in with no success.

‌

I checked developer tools network tab and it seems that the request is

{code}
DELETE https://bitbucket.org/!api/1.0/repositories/ronkot/birder/deploy-keys/
{code}

Just guessing, but shouldn’t the path contain also id for the key to be deleted?

When using the postman to test the endpoint,

/2.0/repositories/{username}/{repo_slug}/pullrequests/{pull_request_id}/approve

with user name and user password for authentication,

{code}
#!plaintext

 Because your Atlassian account admin requires single sign-on, you&#x27;ll need to authenticate with an app password. Create an app password at https://bitbucket.org/account/admin/app-passwords

{code}

When using user name and app password ->

{code}
#!plaintext
This endpoint does not support token-based authentication
{code}

What&#x27;s the proper way to access the API?

Currently, if you change the assignee of an Issue on Bitbucket’s Issues page, that will leave a comment containing the whole Issue description again, which depending the size of the description might impact the usability of that feature.

Would be nice to have rather than:

{code}
User

* assigned issue to New User

The whole issue description.
{code}

Something just like:

{code}
User

* assigned issue to New User
{code}
